-- THE TRIGGER. COMPACT folds the flushed components into one large component via the
-- MERGE path (ColumnBTreeBulkloader.persist -> writeColumnsPages). The merged component's
-- .dic spans multiple LAF pages (fat columns -> many data pages); page-zero is written
-- LAST (low LAF id) so a higher LAF page flushes first -> out-of-order append to the
-- append-only cloud .dic writer -> AbstractCloudIOManager.ensurePosition throws
-- "Misaligned positions" -> MERGE thread halts the JVM.

USE test;

COMPACT DATASET ColumnDataset;
